aa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ngambaa\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"olympic boxing\", \"from\": 2056, \"to\": 2070}, {\"ngram\": \"its first ever medalist\", \"from\": 2086, \"to\": 2109}, {\"ngram\": \"the 75kg weight\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s\", \"from\": 2175, \"to\": 2194}, {\"ngram\": \"semifinals\", \"from\": 2195, \"to\": 2205}, {\"ngram\": \"at least a bronze medal\", \"from\": 2226, \"to\": 2249}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s tennis, the young Spaniard, Carlos Alcaraz, faced off against the legendary Novak Djokovic of Serbia, in what was a rematch of the 2024 Wimbledon championship.\", \"from\": 2252, \"to\": 2422, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2291, \"end\": 2305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carlos Alcaraz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s\", \"from\": 2255, \"to\": 2262}, {\"ngram\": \"tennis\", \"from\": 2263, \"to\": 2269}, {\"ngram\": \"the young Spaniard\", \"from\": 2271, \"to\": 2289}, {\"ngram\": \"the legendary Novak Djokovic\", \"from\": 2325, \"to\": 2353}, {\"ngram\": \"Serbia\", \"from\": 2357, \"to\": 2363}, {\"ngram\": \"a rematch\", \"from\": 2377, \"to\": 2386}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Wimbledon championship\", \"from\": 2390, \"to\": 2421}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, this time around, it was Djokovic who won the tournament, bringing home gold for Serbia.\", \"from\": 2424, \"to\": 2521, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2458, \"end\": 2466, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 0.9999998863170341, \"rank\": 1.1368303267217567e-07, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"db